            <div class="col-md-9">
                <p>This is an extension from one of my academic project on iOS. It could be downloaded and run either on an Xcode siulator or a real iOS device (Apple developer account required). It failed to be released because of copyrigh issue :(</p>

                <p>Two players could connect via Bluetooth or Apple Game Center. During a two-player game, one device are selected as the server to decide the game logic. The rules are like original Tetris, but two players are playing on the same field at the same time. They also share one Next shape, so who drops current shape fast will get Next shape. Sometimes blocks in a shape has properties, such as a Bomb that will blow up surrounding blocks when it is dropped. When a row is removed, each player obtains score based on his number of removing blocks. Finally when the game ends, who has more scores wins!</p>

                <p>I start my undergrad study as a finance student, and this is the first completly working program with GUI I built up after I switched into Computer Science. It really means a lot to me. By that time I still didn't know how to use version control. Github is just somewhere storing code to me, so I just finish everything and upload the project at one time.</p>
